		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Ah okay this is usefull to know. So yeah if you have to pay ~$1k only to submit a game it's quite not possible if you don't mass sell it. Of course for actual video game retailers this is few things but heh, again nobody here is one of them.
<br />It may be possible to add a false rating on your website before downloading, corresponding to the content of the game, and it's not likely anyone will notice that. But it could be illegal to do so.
<br />
<br />I've read that it was illegal to use (R) or TM symbols if you did not actually register a trade mark, and that you could have to pay a fee if you are caught doing that. It's fun because I'm pretty sure I have done that at least once without suspecting that. However the use of (C) is free for anyone who wants to copyright one of his creations.

		

