	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Small-volume publishers of video games that meet these criteria  can use <a href="http://www.tigrs.org/" class="postlink">TIGRS</a> self-certification for free instead of paying ESRB/PEGI.
<br /><ul><li>The game is not sold through major retailers. Instead, try online sales or sales in specialty stores. </li><li>The game is for an "open" platform, or it is for one that has been suitably cracked and is no longer supported by the console maker. These include Linux, Windows, Mac OS X, Pocket PC, NES, Mega Drive/Genesis, Dreamcast, and Game Boy Advance. </li><li>The game is sold in a country whose legislation does not mandate a particular video game rating system. Such countries include the United States. </li></ul>

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


